<HEADLINE> NATO, Central Asian States to Conduct Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Central Asian peace-keeping
forces from seven nations will hold a joint military exercise
codenamed "97' Central-Asia Forces" with NATO in Kazakhstan and
Uzbekistan in mid-September, reports from Kazakh News Agency said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Troops from Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan, Russia, the
U.S. and Turkey, which make up the Central Asian peace-keeping
force, will take part in the exercise, which will be carried out
in two stages in Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan. 
