<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Unemployment Rate Reaches Record 33 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's unemployment rate reached a
record 33 percent in 1996 while the population in absolute poverty
was 40 percent, a Zimbabwe country profile document said today.
</P>
<P>
The document, prepared for the UN General Assembly Special
Session on Environment and Sustainable Development, said the country
had a high incidence of poverty in 1995 when about 62 percent of the
population was classified as poor and 46 percent as very poor.
</P>
<P>
The document said 20 percent of public spending in 1996 was
on social sectors while the national poverty level was 60 percent
during the same period.
</P>
<P>
The country profile is an overview of Zimbabwe's efforts
undertaken since 1992 in respect of individual chapters of Agenda 21,
the first earth summit blueprint for sustainable development adopted
in Rio de Janeiro. enditem

