<HEADLINE> British Exports to Zimbabwe Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- British exports to Zimbabwe last year
increased by 18 percent, with goods worth an average 16.3
million US dollars being brought into the country each month, it
was learnt today.
</P>
<P>
According to a document compiled by the Zimbabwe Investment
Centre, Barclays Bank and Standard Chartered Bank, Zimbabwe's exports
to Britain were about 20 percent higher.
</P>
<P>
The document said, ''Britain is also by far the largest foreign
investor in Zimbabwe, with 300 firms in the country which are wholly
or partially owned by British-based companies.''
</P>
<P>
The 300 British firms in Zimbabwe are collectively worth 286
million US dollars. enditem

