<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Company Offers Wireless Internet Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 23 (Xinhua) -- CellularVision USA announced
today that it has begun marketing a new wireless high-speed
Internet access product, which it hopes to stay ahead of the
industry for long.
</P>
<P>
Called CellularVision Digital Network(SM) or CVDN 500, the
product uses wireless LMDS technology. The service enables
consumers to bypass over-burdened telephone lines to access the
Internet at 500 kbps -- four times the speed of an ISDN line (128
kbps) and about 20 times the speed of a typical consumer's 28.8
kbps modem.
</P>
<P>
The cost of installation and monthly access are affordable for
commercial and home users, according to the New York-based
company.
</P>
<P>
The technology's highly flexible nature will allow CVUS to stay
ahead of the market, and the company will offer such Internet
access at even higher speeds in early 1998, the company said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the company also announced recently that it has
signed an agreement with NYNEX, the local telephone company, which
will allow it to bundle local telephone service to consumers along
with its high-speed Internet access and subscription television
service.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
