<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host SADC Transport Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe National Chamber of
Commerce (ZNCC) today said it will hold a Southern African
Development Community (SADC) regional conference next month on
harmonization of transport and communication systems.
</P>
<P>
The chamber said that inter-state transport and communications
infrastructure are "grossly" inadequate to support the level of
market integration and intra-regional trade envisaged.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, the strategy for economic integration recognizes
the need to develop adequate transport and communications
facilities as a prerequisite for economic development in general
and for the expansion of intra-regional trade in particular," it
said.
</P>
<P>
Target groups include government officials, ministries of
transport and of posts and telecommunications, transport
operators, chambers of commerce, trade associations, trade
unions, importers and exporters, freight forwarders and other
associations with similar functions.
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed will include harmonization of freight
market access policies on the SADC region, elimination of
regional operational constraints, the role of regional
governments in facilitating efficient transport networks and
harmonization of road transport tariffs under the Common Market
for East and Southern Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
