<HEADLINE> Nigerian Government Pledges Lasting Solution to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government today said
that it is taking "urgent and drastic measures" to solve the
issue of fuel scarcity that has paralyzed the country's economic
and social life.
</P>
<P>
The country's No. 2 leader, Chief of General Staff
Lieutenant-General Oladipo Diya, told reporters in Abuja today
that the government is aware that Nigerians are feeling really
bad about it.
</P>
<P>
He said the Defense and Security Council will meet today in
Abuja to discuss the issue, and will try to find a lasting
solution to it.
</P>
<P>
The fuel scarcity in Nigeria has caused wide confusion and
huge losses in the last few months. Commuters are stranded at
many bus stops. Some people have to go off their work earlier
because they have to walk for home. Many simply choose to stay at
home.
</P>
<P>
The persistent fuel scarcity has caused a war of words between
Petroleum Minister Chief Dan Etete and Finance Minister Anthony
Ani about the cause of the problem.
</P>
<P>
Lagos State Administrator Colonel Mohammed Marwa has also said
that for a major oil producer like Nigeria, the fuel scarcity is
not only embarrassing, but also scandalous. item

