<HEADLINE> Mortgage Rates Drop Further in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Canada's mortgage rates are
dropping further, this time led by Royal Bank of Canada.
</P>
<P>
Canada's biggest commercial bank Royal Bank announced today
that it is lowering rates for long-term residential mortgage of
five, seven, 10 and 25 years by 0.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
That drops a five-year mortgage to seven percent and a 25-year
mortgage to 8.85 percent.
</P>
<P>
"For a five year mortgage for 100,000 dollars amortized over 25
years, this means a decrease in payments of nine dollars a month,"
the bank said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Other Canadian commercial banks are expected to follow suit
soon.
</P>
<P>
The latest drop follows decrease earlier this month on mortgage
terms ranging from six months to five years.
</P>
<P>
Mortgage rates have been dropping as a result of lower interest
rates of bond market, where banks raise mortgage money. 
</P>
