<HEADLINE> Nemtsov on Russia-China Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian First Deputy Prime Minister
Boris Nemtsov said here today that a package of economic
agreements would be signed during the visit of Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin to Beijing, scheduled for June 26-28.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference on Monday, Nemtsov, who leaves
for Beijing tonight to prepare for Chernomyrdin's visit, said that
the bilateral agreements include, among others, the agreements on
cooperation in power engineering, gas extraction in China, border
trade, and cultural exchanges, as well as some documents
concerning bilateral economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov expressed hope that Russia and China will resolve the
problem of mutual payments and move on to "civilized trade
relations". He regretted that the trade volume between Russia and
China is only 6.8 billion US dollars, saying it should be "much
bigger."
</P>
<P>
He noted that several years ago barter deal accounted for 60
percent of bilateral trade turnover, but now they have dropped to
12-14 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the Russian leader, during the visit the Russian
and Chinese ministries of railways are expected to sign an
agreement on cooperation to regulate the transit of cargoes from
the Far East to Europe via China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Ministry of Fuel and Energy and the Chinese
national oil and gas corporation also plan to sign an agreement
with a focus on the construction of gas and oil pipelines from
Russia to South Korea and Japan via Mongolia and China.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov also expressed hope that Russia will take part in great
projects of China to build some power plants on the Yangtze river.
It is said that Russia, the United States, Canada, France and
Japan are participating in a tender for the right to supply
equipment for these power plants.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency quoted Nemtsov's press secretary
Andrei Pershin as saying on Monday that during the visit Nemtsov
is expected to meet Chinese Premier Li Peng, Deputy Premier Li
lanqing, State Planning Committee Chairman Chen Jinhua, and Liu
Yumei, President of the corporation in charge of the Three Valley
electric station construction project.
</P>
<P>
Staying in Beijing, Nemtsov also intends to raise the question
of illegal migration of Chinese citizens to Russia. Besides, he
will discuss with Chinese officials Russia-China military
cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
