signed two agreements with the Arab Financing Program (AFP) and
the oil-poor kingdom was thus provided with 12.5 million dollars
of credit from the AFP.
</P>
<P>
The UAE is among the Arab countries that severed ties with
Jordan during the 1991 Gulf War to drive Iraqi troops from
Kuwait. But in the recent years the bilateral ties have begun to
improve since the kingdom distanced itself politically away from
Iraq. 
