<HEADLINE> Hingis Sails into Second Round at Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WIMBLEDON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis
of Switzerland enjoyed a smooth sailing into the second round of
the Wimbledon Tennis Chamipionship here this afternoon by
defeating Anne Kremer of Luxembourg in straight sets 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Despite of fierce resistance from her strong opponent, the
16-year-old Hingis, also the women's top seed, played some
astonishing tennis and finally snatched her first victory.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, eight seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicarrio of
Spain also overwhelmed her British opponent Clare Wood of
Britain 6-0, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
In the men's events, seventh seed Mark Philippoussis of
Austrialia, regarded as one of the most powerful servers, was
beaten by Britain's non-seeded player G Rusedski 6-7, 6-7, 4-6,
creating largest upset of the Championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
