<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges Different Areas To Fight Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- China's State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters and the Ministry of Water Resources
jointly issued an urgent notice today asking different areas to
work hard on drought relief.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of June, many parts north of the Yangtze
River have been plagued by high temperatures and little rainfall,
while record high temperatures hit northern China and western
parts of northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The drought has caused damage to about 17.3 million ha of
crops, 5.8 million ha of which were hit by a severe drought, the
notice said. In late June most parts of north China will have less
rainfall, it noted, and the middle and lower reaches of the
Yangtze River will also suffer from a summer drought.
</P>
<P>
The notice called on areas to take immediate steps to fight the
drought in the following ways:
</P>
<P>
-- Not being overjoyed by a summer harvest that was partly due
to good spring weather, but getting ready instead for the next
harvest in spite of the drought.
</P>
<P>
-- Taking steps to make the most of limited water resources and
to plant as much as is allowable.
</P>
<P>
-- Drought relief organizations should do all they can to
provide farmers with services.
</P>
<P>
-- Departments concerned should be sure that all the capital,
fuels, and other materials needed are available.
</P>
<P>
-- Flood control and drought relief preparations should be made
simultaneously for large rivers and reservoirs for the flood
season.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
