<HEADLINE> Uganda to Hold State Funeral for Akii-Bua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's only Olympic gold
medallist John Akii-Bua, who died last week, will be accorded a
state funeral on Thursday, the government announced in Kampala,
Uganda, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the ministry of internal affairs said Akii-Bua
will be given full state honours and flags will fly at half mast
across Uganda on Thursday, which has been declared a national day
of mourning.
</P>
<P>
Akii-Bua, who won the 400 meters hurdles at the 1972 Munich in
47.82 seconds, will be laid to rest at his home village in
northern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Akii-Bua, aged 49, died last Friday night after complaining of
abdominal pains.  
</P>
</TEXT>
