<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News in Brief on Hong Kong Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Following is the news in brief on
activities related to the return of Hong Kong to the motherland:
</P>
<P>
 Beijing to Be Lit-Up
</P>
<P>
Workers are busying installing lights on 91 large buildings and
flyovers, on Tian'anmen Square, and along the Avenue of Chang'an
to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The work will be completed by June 25 and the square and the
avenue are scheduled to be turned into a sea of lights on June 28.
</P>
<P>
 Busy Flag, Emblem Designer
</P>
<P>
Professor Xiao Hong, who won first prize for his design for the
flags and emblems of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
and the Macao Special Administrative Region, has been too busy to
take a break these days.
</P>
<P>
Almost every local meeting connected to Hong Kong's return in
Zhengzhou City, the capital of Henan Province where Xiao lives had
asked him to be present, until recently, when the poor man fell
ill and was hospitalized for nine days because of fatigue.
</P>
<P>
 Color TV Buying Spree
</P>
<P>
Farmers in Ruijin City in east China's Jiangxi Province, are
mobbing local shops to buy color TV sets to get a colorful look at
the grand handover ceremony that will be broadcast live.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of June, over 2,000 rural households have
purchased color TVs, and local governments have expanded the local
cable-tv networks to 80 percent of the city. Ruijin was a
Communist Party-led revolutionary base in the 1930s.
</P>
<P>
 Farmers' Stamp Show
</P>
<P>
A stamp exhibition is being held by farmers in a small village
near Hohhot, the capital of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region,
to mark the return of Hong Kong and the 50th anniversary of the
founding of Inner Mongolia as the country's first ethnic minority
autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Genxi, head of the village, said that he hopes the two
special places, Inner Mongolia and Hong Kong, can increase
cooperation after Hong Kong's return to the motherland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
