<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- A black American named Joseph Morris has been
detained and put in prison for unlawful entry into Iran, Iranian
judiciary chief revealed here today.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran announced today that it will soon start the
trial of German companies which offered chemical weapons to Iraq
during the Iran-Iraq war in 1980s.
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- Sri Lankan government troops Monday night
recaptured Puliyankulam, a key town in the north of the country
and 204 kilometers from Colombo, military sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Tihomir Blaskic, a former general of Bosnian Croat
militia, went on trial Tuesday at the United Nations War Crimes
Tribunal in the Hague, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Some 80 Rwandans responsible for massacre in 1994 in
their native country joined the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) in
Uganda, a report reaching here said today. 
</P>
