<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boeing Sees Market Growth In HK and China's Inland Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Boeing Co. of the United
States has full confidence in the airline industries of Hong Kong
and China's inland areas, a senior company official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Hong Kong International Aerospace Forum, Michael
Zimmerman, president of Boeing China, said that sustained economic
growth in Hong Kong and China's inland areas will promote the
development of airline industries there.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that, in the next 20 years, airline industries in
China's interior areas and Hong Kong will record an annual average
increase of 8.7 percent, double that of the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the number of people flying into and out of
China will rise sharply, far exceeding the annual growth of 4.9
percent in the number of travelers globally," he said.
</P>
<P>
The aviation market in China's inland areas will be one with
the fastest growth in the world, he said. "Our latest estimates
indicate that the aviation market in China's inland areas will
expand at an annual growth of 10.3 percent on average and that the
market in 2016 will be seven times as large as that of today."
</P>
<P>
"Naturally, that is good news for Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that, "as an international financial and
commercial center, Hong Kong will play an increasingly important
role in the economic development of China's inland areas after its
return to China (on July 1 this year), and in return it will
benefit from the economic growth in the inland areas."
</P>
<P>
All these demonstrate that Hong Kong will continue to play its
role as the hub of airline industries in the Asia-Pacific region,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
