<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Executive Council Decided Package of Remunerations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Council (ExCo) of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) today
announced the decision on package remunerations concerning some
members of the bodies of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The decision was based on the recommendations from the
Independent Commission on Remuneration for Members of the
Executive Council and the Legislature of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Chief Executive Office of the HKSAR said
that the Executive Council has taken into account the nature and
volume of the workload of the Chief Executive, the Executive
Council and the Provisional Legislature, both before and after
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that the HKSAR ExCo decided that the Chief Executive's
remuneration will be the same as the existing package for the Hong
Kong governor (whose monthly salary is 253,312.5 HK dollars),
including leave, passages, and medical benefits.
</P>
<P>
As a local person, the Chief Executive should pay income tax on
his salary, non-accountable entertainment allowance and contract
gratuity.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive should also pay excise duty on alcoholic
beverages purchased for official entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the HKSAR ExCo also endorsed the
recommendation of the Independent Commission that members of the
Provisional Legislature should be paid a lump sum of 100,000 HK
dollars for their service between February and June 1997, adding
that members who also serve on the existing Legislative Council
will receive half the amount, i.e. 50,000 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said that the provision for the president of the Legislative
Council is doubled to 200,000 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chief Executive has accepted the Commission's
recommendation that non-official members of the HKSAR ExCo should
receive the same amount of taxable honorarium as existing ExCo
members, which is 66,270 HK dollars a month.
</P>
<P>
The convenor of the HKSAR ExCo, like the former senior member
of ExCo, is entitled to a higher level of honorarium of 106,110 HK
dollars. This is to give recognition to his role in coordinating
among the non-official members and assisting the Chief Executive
in taking forward ExCo-related matters.
</P>
<P>
The Independent Commission was appointed in March this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
