is giving 200 million U.S. dollars in cash to establish a
foundation that will bring computers into public libraries in
low-income areas throughout the U.S. and Canada.
</P>
<P>
-- The supreme Court Monday declined to hear a Clinton
administration appeal of a lower court ruling forcing White
House lawyers to give Whitewater independent counsel Kenneth
Starr notes they took in discussions with Hillary Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The Dow Jones industrials tumbled 192.25 Monday, its
second biggest point drop ever, as traders interpreted comments
by Japan's prime minister as a threat Japanese investors may
begin large-scale sales of U.S. stocks and bonds. 
</P>
