<HEADLINE> Fighting Intensified in Brazzaville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fighting has broken out
again in the Congolese capital Brazzaville between the troops of
President Pascal Lissouba and militia soldiers of former
president Sassou Ngyesso, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged artillery fire for about two hours
near the Brazzaville International Airport. It is the worst
violation so far of a week old ceasefire, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Parliament Building, where a new constitutional
council will be sworn in, was also attacked, and so was a military
camp near Kinshasa, the capital of the neighboring Democratic
Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of eight west African countries meeting in Togo have
pledged to provide troops for peace keeping force to be sent to
Brazzaville. 
</P>
