<HEADLINE> S. Africa Deputy Minister Briefed on Lesotho's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho High Commissioner to
South Africa Lincoln Mokose has briefed South African Deputy
Foreign Affairs Minister Aziz Pahad on tension between political
parties in Lesotho, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued in Pretoria by the Department of Foreign
Affairs of South Africa confirmed the meeting between Mokose and
Pahad on Monday, but did not elaborate on their discussions.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Lesotho Prime Minister Ntsu Mokhehle
resigned from his ruling Basotholand Congress Party (BCP) to form
a new party, the Lesotho Congress for Democracy (LCD), and
transferred the government power to the newly formed party.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle's move stunned the small land-locked kingdom, forcing
opposition parties to form a coalition with the BCP, which
condemned the move and termed it unconstitutional, said the
reports.
</P>
<P>
The coalition called for the resignation of Mokhehle and
planned a series of protest actions in Maseru, capital of the
kingdom, making the situation even worse.
</P>
<P>
On Monday,South African Foreign Affairs Minister Alfred Nzo,
who met Lesotho government officials a few days earlier, said
South Africa would be prepared to help resolve the conflict
between Lesotho's political parties if it was asked to do so.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Lesotho high commissioners in Zimbabwe and Botswana
had also been instructed to brief their host governments on the
situation in Lesotho, the source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
