<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Official on Housing Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor Li Tieying
told a recent symposium on housing reform of some provinces and
municipalities that reforms should be intensified along with the
acceleration of housing construction in urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, told those gathered for the symposium in Baotou City,
in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region that civil housing should
become a new economic growth area and a new consuming area.
</P>
<P>
He called for further implementation of various reform
policies, saying that since the economic situation is sound it
provides a good opportunity to increase them.
</P>
<P>
An efforts should be made to apply the system of raising funds
for housing publically in more places, and that some enterprises,
institutions, and cities with better conditions should halt the
practice of providing housing for employees as welfare, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He urged related departments and institutions at all levels to
draw up plans to help people with special difficulties buy houses.
</P>
<P>
"A housing management system that caters to the socialist
market economy should be set up as soon as possible," Li
stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
