<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Urges Enterprise Groups To Play Bigger Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng, meeting in
Beijing today with leaders of eight enterprise groups, said that
enterprise reforms should be combined with reorganization,
renovation, and improved management in state-owned companies.
</P>
<P>
This is in keeping with the goal of setting up a modern
enterprise system to make enterprise groups play a bigger role in
economic development and restructuring, he said.
</P>
<P>
Developing enterprise groups not only meets the need of the
country's economic development but also is a trend in world
economic development, Li said.
</P>
<P>
These groups should be formed in accordance with their
situation and under the guidance of the state's macro-economic
controls and policy, he said, noting that 120 enterprises have
been approved by the State Council to test the group policy.
</P>
<P>
The 120 firms account for a fourth of the total assets, sales
and pre-tax profits of all state-owned enterprises, while their
net profits exceed half the total, Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
