<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hkhk-HKTDC to Hold Seminars on Global Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Trade Development
Council(TDC) will host 17 seminars on the global market at the
Extension to the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center from
July 10 to 12, TDC announced today.
</P>
<P>
These seminars, to be held during TDC's Market Day Exhibition,
will be the Extension's first public seminar series after its
completion.
</P>
<P>
"The series will update local businessmen on the global trading
climate and development strategies of local small and medium
enterprises," said TDC's deputy senior manager of information
services, Lai Ching-hung.
</P>
<P>
The seminars will focus on analyses of Hong Kong's post-1997
economic and trade developments, business opportunities and
preferential treatment for overseas investors in the interior
areas in China, finance, information technology, and foreign trade
practices in the U.S. and emerging markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
