<HEADLINE> Shanghai ATMs Links up With Visa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Automatic tellers' machines (ATM)
in Shanghai, China's financial center, were hooked up today with
the Visa/Plus network.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, Visa card-holders worldwide can
draw cash directly from ATMs in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 1,100 ATMs run by eight financial
institutions on major streets in the city, 80 of which provide the
service for international clients.
</P>
<P>
Visa International is the world's largest credit card issuer,
with 700 million card holders worldwide and one trillion US
dollars in business last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
