<HEADLINE> Troops In Xinjiang Asked To Remain On Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region is a large area with a long border and soldiers there must
maintain a high state of alert, Vice-chairman of the Central
Military Commission General Chi Haotian said during an inspection
tour of the region June 21-23.
</P>
<P>
Chi had just returned from an overseas trip when he made the
visit.
</P>
<P>
In conversations with soldiers, he asked them to increase their
drills and patrols to build a peaceful, safe, stable and strong
frontier.
</P>
<P>
The general, who is also State Councilor and Defense Minister,
spoke highly of the current solidarity in Xinjiang and urged the
troops to make a greater contribution to reforms, development and
stability there. 
</P>
