<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hkhk - HK's Airport Authority Signs Duty Free Liquor, Tobacco Licence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Airport Authority
(AA) and Sky Connection Ltd. signed here Tuesday a licence
agreement for duty free liquor and Tobacco operations at Hong Kong
Sky Mall at the new airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
The mall is a world-class shopping mall which will serve
travelers and airport users inside the new airport's passenger
terminal.
</P>
<P>
The licence is the largest of its kind in the world. Sky
Connection is a joint venture between two major local
conglomerates, The Lai Sun Group and The New World Group. The
former is a shareholder in the consortium operating the duty free
liquor and tobacco concession at the existing airport at Kai Tak.
</P>
<P>
The licence includes a total of 12 departures level outlets -
two pre-order landside units and 10 duty-free airside units - plus
one storage unit.
</P>
<P>
This is currently the only duty free licence at the new airport
and it gives the licensee the right to sell and distribute a
comprehensive range of duty-free spirits, wines, beer, cigarettes,
cigars and pipe tobacco to departing, transfer and other transit
passengers. The licence period is 62 months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
