<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Religious Circle Greets HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Religious groups in Beijing who
held a symposium today to greet the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland said that the return of Hong Kong will not only erase
the Chinese nation's disgrace of suffering from foreign
aggression, but will also inspire members of religious groups to
strive for the peaceful reunification and prosperity of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Puchu, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), spoke
about how Hong Kong was ceded to Britain and how the struggles of
the Chinese people against foreign invaders began.
</P>
<P>
He praised the "one country, two systems" concept, saying that
it will help maintain the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong as
well as world peace, and will increase international exchanges and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, who is president of the Buddhist Association of China,
said that religious groups can use the event for education in
patriotism and the "one country, two systems" concept among their
people.
</P>
<P>
Ye Xiaowen, director of the Bureau of Religious Affairs of the
State Council, said the return of Hong Kong is a mirror of
history, and a lively textbook on patriotism.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was organized by the United Front Work Department
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, the
Subcommittee of Ethnic and Religious Affairs of the CPPCC National
Committee, and the Bureau of Religious Affairs of the State
Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
