<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Passes Law on Foreigners' Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Russia's lower house of parliament
today passed a law defining the rights of foreigners in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma passed the law by 247 votes to 30. The
legislation states that foreign citizens and Russians with dual
nationality have no right to hold national and local office nor to
serve on the crew of military or non-commercial boats and
aircrafts.
</P>
<P>
Foreign citizens can live permanently in Russia only with
permission and the federal government must guarantee priority for
Russians in finding work by deciding annually the number of
foreigners allowed to work in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
