<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Traffic Accidents in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were killed and
many others injured in three separate traffic accidents in India
in the past 24 hours, Press Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
Four people, including a woman, were killed on the spot and 47
injured when a bus and mini-bus collided with each other in
India's Kerala state this morning.
</P>
<P>
In a traffic accident in India's Andhra Pradesh on Monday,
eight persons died when an overcrowded van in which they were
traveling turned turtle.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the bus carrying 70 passengers lost control and
dashed the vehicle against a tree while negotiating a curve.
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday, four women were buried alive and 15 others
injured when a loaded truck overturned in India's Bihar state.
</P>
