<HEADLINE> Commentary: The World Has Confidence in Hong Kong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua News Agency today published a
commentary on the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, entitled
"The World Has Confidence in Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
Over 8,000 journalists from around the globe are now gathering
in Hong Kong. As the day for the return of Hong Kong approaches,
the territory has become the focus of world opinion. Listening to
the current tide of talk and discussion over Hong Kong, we are
deeply impressed that people from all walks of life place great
confidence in the future development of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The world is watching Hong Kong, for the return of Hong Kong to
the motherland is an extraordinary event in world history. It
serves as an example to the international community of a way to
peacefully resolving historical disputes between countries; it
signals an end to the colonial rule of Britain in the
continent of Asia; and it is a turning point from which peace and
development in Asia and even the whole world could be improved.
</P>
<P>
The world is watching Hong Kong, for it is a global economic
center where a host of countries direct investment and encourage
trade relations, and where all countries find their respective
interests connected to this stable and prosperous land.
</P>
<P>
The world has confidence in Hong Kong, because people have as
much confidence in the principle of "One Country, Two Systems."
Looking back upon the year 1984 when the Sino-British Joint
Declaration was signed, the then British Prime Minister Margaret
Thatcher applauded the peaceful settlement of the Hong Kong issue,
attributing it to Deng Xiaoping's brilliant concept of "One
Country, Two Systems."
</P>
<P>
The following 13 years has witnessed both social stability and
continual economic development achieved in Hong Kong. All
countries around the globe, in turn, benefit from the stability
and prosperity in Hong Kong. All these testify to the truth that
the policy of "One Country, Two Systems" tallies with the
practical situation, and is in full accordance with that required
of the development of Hong Kong. The goal of long-term prosperity
and stability is sure to be realized with the implementation of
the principle of "One Country, Two Systems."
</P>
<P>
The world has confidence in Hong Kong, because people have
confidence in the stability and the economic development prospects
in China. People rest assured that the Chinese government will
fulfill the Sino-British Joint Declaration and strictly abide by
the Basic Law.
</P>
</TEXT>
