<HEADLINE> Commentary: The World Has Confidence in Hong Kong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The world has confidence in Hong Kong, because people are
optimistic towards the economic development prospects in Hong
Kong. According to the headquarters of the World Trade
Organization (WTO), a group of internationally prestigious
organizations that specialize in evaluating economic freedom
status, ranked Hong Kong in first place. At the beginning of June,
the "World Economic Tribune" elected Hong Kong as the second most
competitive economic system throughout the world. During the first
half of this year, Hong Kong registered over 20,000 new companies,
324 of which were opened by foreigners, a 12 percent rise compared
with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
It is due to people's confidence in Hong Kong that investment
from various countries is increasing; It is due to people's
confidence in Hong Kong that 34 countries have granted Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) the visa-free treatment; And
it is due to people's confidence in Hong Kong that nearly a
thousand political VIPs and celebrities from all countries will
attend the handover ceremony and the inauguration ceremony of SAR.
</P>
<P>
Because it will return to the motherland, Hong Kong is
receiving unprecedentedly close attention; Because it will return
to the motherland, Hong Kong is winning honors never thought of
before; Because it will return to the motherland, Hong Kong is
gaining new opportunities for development. With the effort of over
six million Hong Kong people, together with the support from its
strong motherland and high-degree attention of the central
government, the concept of "One Country, Two Systems" will
undoubtedly achieve successful implementation in Hong Kong, and
the territory's long-term stability and prosperity will come true
in all likelihood. 
</P>
