<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Conchita Martinez, who won
the Wimbledon in 1994, brushed aside Karina Habsudova of Slovakia
in less than an hour in the first round of the Wimbledon tennis
championships on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 10th-seeded Martinez, scored an impressive 6-1, 6-2 victory
over her 17th-ranked opponent.
</P>
<P>
