world rankings following a series of disappointing results, will
next play the winner of the all-Japanese clash between Yuka
Yoshida and Rika Hiraki.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Anke Huber, the seventh-seed, proved too powerful for
Japanese qualifier Hiruka Inoue and prevailed 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Huber now faces a seond-round clash against either Joannette
Kruger of South Africa or Stephanie De Ville of Belgium.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches, American Nicole Arendt defeated Petra
Langrova of the Czech Republic 6-2, 6-0. 
