<HEADLINE> Building A Mighty, Civilized Force to Be Stationed in Hong Kong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army
(PLA) troops to be stationed in Hong Kong are strictly following
requirements set for the whole army by Jiang Zemin, Chairman of
the Central Military Commission (CMC), that they be qualified
politically, competent militarily, have fine style of work, strict
discipline and adequate logistical support.
</P>
<P>
A working group of the CMC and the PLA's General Staff
Headquarters, General Political Department, and General Logistics
Department recently examined the troops' performance and found
their military and political quality, awareness of legal affairs,
level of culture, and logistic support up to high standard. They
were found to have acquired the ability to carry out the duty that
they are sworn to in the defense of Hong Kong in an exemplary way.
</P>
<P>
They were established on the basis of Deng Xiaoping's concept
of "One Country, Two Systems" and are a strong ground, naval and
air force.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Communist Party's Central Committee and the CMC
have paid a great deal of attention to building the force and have
placed great importance on it. Jiang Zemin and other CMC leaders
have visited the troops repeatedly to inspect them and guide their
work.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized the high standards and strict requirements for
the PLA Hong Kong troops and said they must be first-class in
ideology, military training, style of work, discipline, education,
and logistic support, and must demonstrate that the PLA is a
mighty and civilized force.
</P>
<P>
The troops have conscientiously followed Jiang's instructions
and have put ideological and political construction at the top of
their agenda. The officers and men have studied Deng Xiaoping's
theory on building socialism with Chinese characteristics and the
Party's basic line to develop their convictions firmly.
</P>
<P>
The officers and men have been taught a revolutionary world
outlook, a sense of duty and of regulations. They have come to
realize that duty and discipline are first and foremost and that
they represent the strength of the country and the military.
</P>
<P>
The PLA troops to be stationed in Hong Kong place great
importance on organizations at the basic level, and 77 companies
have been chosen as advanced units, while 28 units and 65 officers
and men have been commended by the CMC, or by the three general
departments of the PLA, or the military area command.
</P>
</TEXT>
