<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- China and Turkey signed a
memorandum of understanding today to strengthen their cooperation
in personnel affairs.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum was signed by Zhang Zhijian, visiting Chinese
vice-minister of personnel affairs and Turgay Ergun, general
director of the Public Administration Institute for Turkish and
the Mideast Affairs.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the document, the two sides will undertake
