<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Building A Mighty, Civilized Force to Be Stationed in Hong Kong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The PLA Hong Kong troops have made improving the culture of
their officers and men the main part of their work. There are
specific regulations on ethics, behaviour, and language of all
officers and men, including drivers, telephone operators, mess
hall personnel, medical workers, and guards. And officers and men
are taught to strictly abide by these rules.
</P>
<P>
In order to educate officers and men about the law, the troops
have organized 37 seminars and more than 40 speech contests and
competitions. They have invited experts who participated in
drafting the Basic Law and the Law Concerning Stationing Troops to
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (the Garrison Law) to
give lectures. They have also published a number of books to
increase legal awareness of the officers and men.
</P>
<P>
All the officers and men have learned the Basic Law, the
Garrison Law, and related laws of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region by heart. In five public demonstrations the
strict discipline and quality of the officers and men of the PLA
Hong Kong troops have won praise from people in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
While placing importance on basic training, the PLA Hong Kong
troops have also engaged in defence training for Hong Kong,
improving their mobility and ability to react to an
emergency. More than 97 percent of them have been rated
"excellent" in 145 training courses.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 officers and men of the ground force have been
praised for their military performance. All boats, ships, and
captains of the naval force have passed training courses. New
aircraft commanders and pilots in the air force have all acquired
all-weather flight capabilities, and new equipment has been
brought up to strength.
</P>
<P>
Logistic support of the PLA Hong Kong troops will be guaranteed
by a rear base in neighboring Shenzhen. An 87-hectare farm built
by them from a tract of overgrown wasteland can produce 290,000
kilograms of vegetables, 53,000 kilograms of eggs, and 25,000
kilograms of fish annually. A modern logistic support system is in
operation.
</P>
<P>
A senior officer of the troops said that they are a
well-trained force, and one that the Party, the motherland and the
people can fully count on.
</P>
<P>
With the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, the PLA Hong
Kong troops will stand in front of the Hong Kong compatriots as a
mighty and civilized force, the officer concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
