<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits West Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.1 on the
Richter Scale hit Jiashi county in northwest China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region at 17:24 (Beijing time) today.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was at 39.5 degrees north latitude and 77.0
degrees east longitude, according to the State Seismological
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The quake was strongly felt in the county seat, but no
casualties or damages have been reported yet.
</P>
<P>
This quake was still one of the aftershocks in a series of
quakes rocking Jiashi county in January this year, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Local seismological departments are keeping a close watch on
the quake activities and the quake-hit area. 
</P>
