<HEADLINE> hkhk - Pakistan Grants Visa-free Access to HKSAR Passport Holders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has decided to grant
visa-free access to the holders of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) passports, according to the
Pakistani Consulate General here today.
</P>
<P>
Holders of the HKSAR passports shall be exempted from visa
requirements for entry into/exit from or transit through the
territory of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan for the duration of
stay not exceeding 30 days, a press release of the consulate
general said.
</P>
<P>
Visa-free access policy will not only ensure unhindered flow of
businessmen and visitors but would also help expand and strengthen
the existing economic and trade linkages between Pakistan and Hong
Kong, said the news release.
</P>
<P>
This policy reflects the confidence of the Pakistani government
in the continued stability, success and prosperity of the HKSAR
beyond 1997, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
