<HEADLINE> Australian Market Holds Up on Wall Street Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market took
a massive overnight tumble on Wall Street in its stride today with
bargain hunters moving in to limit losses.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the All Ordinaries Index was down 17.9 points to
2688.4.
</P>
<P>
In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average slumped as rising
interest rates spurred a rush of profit-taking on the stock
market's record-setting advance, dropping 192.25 points to close
at 7,604.26.
</P>
<P>
"I think the Australian market did probably better than
expected," a D&AMP;D Tolhurst analyst said.
</P>
<P>
"It's been an interesting market. You might say that most of
the day, we did between 32 and about five points down, but in the
last half an hour, it went down another 10 points."
</P>
<P>
"It was a good accumulation day."
</P>
<P>
Blue chip miner BHP's stock ended 10 cents lower at 19.4
Australian dollars, "a pretty good performance," one broker said.
</P>
<P>
Oil major Woodside Petroleum's shares closed off 40.2 cents at
10.47 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rio Tinto finished the day on a positive note, with its shares
up 10.4 cents at 22.554 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Banks ended the day negatively, with the index dropping 29.4
points to 4827.4.
</P>
<P>
ANZ's shares fell 7 cents to 9.66 Australian dollars, with
Westpac's off 12 cents at 7.8 Australian dollars, CBA's 7 cents at
15.41 Australian dollars and NAB's 7.4 cents at 18.83 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrial Index shed 24.8 points to 4228.3 at the
market's close, while the All Resources slipped 13 points to
1501.1.
</P>
<P>
The gold index was down five points to 1480.1.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 341.71 million shares valued at 804.20
million Australian dollars (603.15 million U.S. dollars) with
falls outnumbering rises 803 to 417.  
</P>
