<HEADLINE> Shandong to Build Largest Water Boiler Production Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Little Duck Group in east
China's Shandong Province will invest massively in the 1996-2000
period, to build a production line with an annual capacity of 1.2
million water-boilers.
</P>
<P>
This will make the company become the largest water-boiler
producer in China, according to market analysts.
</P>
<P>
The company will complete its project this year, and the key
technology and equipment will be introduced from Italy.
</P>
<P>
Market specialists say that China will need at least six
million water boilers annually in the coming years, because of the
growing income of both rural and urban residents.
</P>
<P>
So far, about 28 percent of the urban families have bought the
machines, and the countryside is also a potential market to be
tapped, they say.
</P>
<P>
Most of the water boilers sold to Chinese families in market
use gas, and the electricity-driven boilers are still rarely seen,
they say.  
