<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Forces Recapture Puliyankulam Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Monday night recaptured Puliyankulam, a key town in the north of
the country and 204 kilometers from Colombo, military sources said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the troops in the Jaya Sikuru (Certain
Victory) operation Monday renewed their operation in the newly
recaptured areas of Nadunkerni and Periyamadu while the aircraft
of the Sri Lankan Air Force engaged the rebel targets, inflicting
heavy casualties on the Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, who put up resistance initially, retreated
northward, since they were unable to face the advancing troops.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from the military, at least 40 rebels were
 killed and more than 70 others injured while one officer and 13
soldiers of the government forces were killed and one officer and
24 soldiers were wounded in action.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of the Jaya Sikuru operation was launched by
the government troops on May 13 to open a key supply line along a
highway from Vavuniya to the Jaffna Peninsula, which runs through
the rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
To date the government troops have managed to recapture 24
kilometers of the highway after heavy fighting with the rebels,
who have been waging a war for a separate Tamil state in the north
and east of the island country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
