<HEADLINE> Hunan Sees Growth of Farm Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The farm insurance business has
developed quickly in central China's Hunan Province, and the local
insurance company's Property sees profit for the first time in
years from the non-profit sector.
</P>
<P>
The premium income of the Hunan Branch of the People's
Insurance Company of China (PICC) generated from the sector
reached 16 million yuan last year, an increase of 30 percent over
that in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Farm insurance has always been a sector with high risks, and it
is a business done by the insurance company before a state farm
insurance company is set up, insurance specialists say.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Chinese insurer has developed 80 kinds of insurance
services to meet different needs, and the total insured volume
reached two billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
The company paid 180 million yuan in compensation for property
losses of local farmers in a serious flood last year, according to
the PICC Property officials.
</P>
<P>
This raised total compensation paid by the company to 350
million yuan last year, to meet the claims by insured farmers,
they said.
</P>
<P>
The company expects a 10 percent growth of business this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
