<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Noted Figure Li Shuyi Passes Away In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Li Shuyi, a member of the China
Democratic league, died of illness in Beijing on June 13 at the
age of 97.
</P>
<P>
Li was born in Changsha, capital of central China's Hunan
province. In October 1924, she married Liu Zhixun, a revolutionary
who was murdered in September 1932.
</P>
<P>
She raised two orphans left by revolutionary martyrs. Since
1977, Li worked in the Central Research Institute of Culture and
History.
</P>
<P>
The farewell ceremony for Li was held yesterday in Beijing,
which was attended by Vice-Premiers Zhu Rongji and Li Lanqing,
together with 500 people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
