<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Hailed for Polio Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has scored the highest
record in Africa against polio in the recent immunisation
campaign, according to a report by a local daily today.
</P>
<P>
"The New Vision" quoted Halib-njie, World Health Organisation
representative to Uganda as saying that Uganda achieved a 95
percent immunisation coverage against polio, the best among
Africa countries.
</P>
<P>
He said Uganda launched the first polio eradication campaign
in December last year, followed by another in January this year.
</P>
<P>
America, which took the same strategy, has rid the continent
of polio, with the last case being recorded in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Similar compaigns are being unrolled in other parts of the
world like China, the Arab world and India where 60 million
chidren were immunised, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He urged all countries to continue to immunise their children
against polio until the last country is free from the virus.
</P>
</TEXT>
