<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Banks Increasing in Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Renminbi Yuan-based business, a
booming banking service in the Pudong New Area, Shanghai, has
become an irresistible business for overseas banks that hope to
enter the China market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 14 overseas banks have moved their China
offices into the Pudong New Area, a promising trade and financial
zone in Shanghai, since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Pudong is the only pilot area in China where overseas banks are
allowed to do Renminbi businesses.
</P>
<P>
According to the rules of the People's Bank of China, the
country's central bank, all the overseas banks have to move their
headquarters in China into Pudong if they hope to get access to do
renminbi business.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Mitsubishi Bank and the American CitiBank moved
into Pudong for the business last year.
</P>
<P>
About 20 more overseas banks are planning to move into Pudong
soon, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
However, only nine of them have been permitted by the central
bank to start yuan-based business with local foreign-funded
enterprises in Shanghai, such as handling deposits and making
loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
