<HEADLINE> Thai Bourse Index Down 11.4 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand
(SET) index today declined 11.4 points from Monday to close at
493.13.
</P>
<P>
Shares worth 5.123 billion baht (204.92 million U.S. dollars)
changed hands in a total of 51,511 transactions.
</P>
<P>
The SET index Monday gained 24.28 points from last Friday to
close at 504.53 with some 218.36 million shares worth 5.589
billion baht (223.56 million dollars) traded in 53,242
transactions.  
</P>
