<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to rise
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained another 6.59 points to close at 2041.38 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 107.81 million units,
valued at 279 million Singapore dollars (about 195.1 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to outnumber advances by 175 to 106
while 341 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Heshe Holdings was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 41.87 million units. It was followed by
Van De Horst which had 23.38 million shares traded. MBf Capital
was next with 6.6 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Sembawang Corporation led the gainers of the day as it rose by
25 cents to finish at 7 Singapore dollars. The Overseas Union Bank
(OUB) Foreign and the Thai Prime Fund picked up by 20 cents each
to end at 9 Singapore dollars and 8.45 U.S. dollars respectively.
OUB Foreign Right closed 15 cents higher at 1.91 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Sungei Way was the biggest loser as it
declined by 78 cents to end at 2.52 Singapore dollars. Creative 50
fell by 70 cents to close at 24 Singapore dollars while MBf
Capital was 62 cents lower at 2.42 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
