<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Cracks down on Drug-Related Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's law enforcement
departments arrested more than 3,200 persons involved in drug
smuggling, stockpiling, production and trafficking in the first
five months of the year.
</P>
<P>
They seized 10.2 kilograms of heroin, 317 kilograms of opium
and 6,973 kilograms of marijuana, the Vietnam News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,669 drug-related cases, 846 were brought to court and
14 death sentences were given and 12 others were sentenced to
life imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
Drug sales are dominated by heroin which makes up 70 percent of
the volume and is sold in places like bars, restaurants and small
stores.
</P>
<P>
Drug traffickers range from taxi drivers to law enforcement
officers and local government officials in border provinces.
</P>
</TEXT>
