<HEADLINE> Banks Finance More Production of Color Tubes in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Bank of
Communications Shanghai Branch and Japan's Tokyo-Mitsubishi Bank
Shanghai Branch today jointly issued a loan to support production
of accessories for color picture tubes in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the loan, worth 45 million yuan,
will be used to finance the installation of a new production line
for producing glass screens and cones for color picture tubes in
Shanghai Asahi Electronic Glass Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
When this project is completed, the company will be able to
generate 1.2 billion yuan of output value and 50 million yuan of
profit annually.
</P>
<P>
The two also signed agreements of cooperation in many fields.
</P>
<P>
Tokyo-Mitsubishi Bank Shanghai Branch is one of the first group
of overseas bank authorized to handle business in Chinese currency
and has so far started more than 150 Renminbi bank accounts.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Communications Shanghai Branch is the Japanese
bank's first cooperation partner in the issue of loans in Chinese
currency of Renminbi yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai company is a joint venture by Shanghai Vacuum
Electron Devices Co. Ltd, Asahi Glass Co. Ltd, Marubeni
Corporation, and Shanghai Jiushi Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Production lines of glass screens and cones by joint ventures
are listed as projects capable of replacing imports, and were
treated as the most important industrial program of 1995. The
installation began the same year.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture began production of glass screens and cones
in tandem with the installation. It scored up 190 million yuan in
sales from glass screens and cones in 1996, and chalked up 330
million yuan in sales of glass screens and cones in the first five
months of this year, saving 2.6 million U.S. dollars for the state
and creating 10 million yuan of profit.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the company will earn a profit of 25
million yuan from sales of glass screens and cones by the end of
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
