<HEADLINE> hkhk-Highway Network in Northwest of Hong Kong Envisaged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A feasibility study on highway construction, which is in
progress, is scheduled to be completed next year, the director
said.
</P>
<P>
According to Leung, Hong Kong now boasts a total of 1,800
kilometers of roads to accommodate 480,000 motor vehicles, with an
average of 270 vehicles per sq km, the highest in the world.
</P>
<P>
Future development of road construction has not only to take
into account the long-term needs and the needs beyond Hong Kong's
administrative lines but also the internal and short-term needs of
Hong Kong itself, Leung said.
</P>
<P>
In view of the impact of expressway networks in adjacent areas
on Hong Kong, such as the already-operational Shenzhen-Guangzhou
and Shenzhen-Shantou expressways, and the expressway that links
between Guangzhou and Zhuhai and Macao, which is still to be
built, it is imperative to add more roads to Hong Kong, the
director noted.
</P>
<P>
One reason for construction of the northwestern highway network,
he said, is to comply with plans for building two new transit
routes connecting Hong Kong with Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
One is a envisaged passage linking the west of Shenzhen with
Hong Kong, and the other is the Lingdingyang Bridge to connect
Zhuhai and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are three highway transit routes linking Hong
Kong with China's interior area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
