<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- About 19 overseas-funded
businesses entered Nantong agricultural zone in east China's
Jiangsu Province, with investment totalling 850 million US dollars
since it was established in October 1995.
</P>
<P>
Situated in Rudong County which is abundant with marine
products, the 30,000 hectares export-oriented agriculture zone
mainly exploits tidal zone resources.
</P>
<P>
