<HEADLINE> Rwanda Killers Join Uganda Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA. June 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 80 Rwandans responsible for
massacre in 1994 in their native country joined the Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) in Uganda, a report reaching here said
today.
</P>
<P>
The group of Hutu militia entered south-western district of
Rukungiri about two months ago, army intelligence sources in
western Kabarole and Bundibugyo districts told "The New Vision".
</P>
<P>
They extracted the conclusion on a close examination of bodies
of the rebels killed in battlefields. Soldiers in frontlines
reported they hearded rebels speaking Rwandese language.
</P>
<P>
A note captured from the rebels said they did not have
ammunitions. Army sources in Bundibugyo district confirmed the
rebels' reaction was "very weak" when they shot at the rebels'
positions.
</P>
<P>
Army sources estimated ADF has some 300 fighters in Bundibugyo
district. The government troops now are combing some forests in
the district to ensure the security for public.
</P>
<P>
A report from Bundibugyo said the rebels burned alive 12
people and killed another ten in the district in the passing two
days.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of civilians evacuated yesterday from the district
as the fighting in the district intensified. The evacuated
reached western town of Fort Portal yesterday at 06:30 pm. The
roads between Fort Portal and Bundibugyo towns are still closed
for civilian transport. 
</P>
