<HEADLINE> Bank Grants Credits to Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian branch of China
Construction Bank has granted credits to 30 enterprises in this
northeast China's port city. It is the first time such banking
services have been offered in China.
</P>
<P>
All enterprises that have been granted credits have credit
ratings of AA or above, and they are promised to get loans and
financial guarantee from the bank as soon as possible within a
year.
</P>
<P>
The maximum loan that these enterprises can obtain from the
bank is 220 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
This is a move taken by the bank to simplify the procedures in
loan-making, bank specialists say. 
</P>
