<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Greets Hong Kong's Return in Varied Ways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Actors and actresses from Beijing,
Shanghai, Hong Kong and northwest China's Shaanxi province will
play in a 29-part TV series depicting China's history of a century
and more related to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Television, video and other cultural companies of Beijing,
Shanghai and Shaanxi invested 9.5 million yuan (over 1.1 million
US dollars) in the TV series.
</P>
<P>
The TV series, namely "one hundred years of vicissitudes", tell
weal and woe to Chinese people in the past 100 years and more from
late Qing Dynasty (1644--1911) to Hong Kong's return on July, 1,
1997 through stories of several generations of two families.
</P>
<P>
A photo exhibition on the roots of Hong Kong's prosperity was
going on in south China's Guangzhou city. On display were Over 380
pictures showing Hong Kong's development and its close ties with
its neighboring province of Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Over 3,000 Chinese oil painters both at home and abroad have
applied for participating in a modern oil painting exhibition
designed to greet Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
A group of judges, including well-known painter Wu Guanzhong,
has selected 193 oil paintings out of the 3,000-strong
participating works for the upcoming exhibition to be held in
Shanghai from June 27 to July 12.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing, capital city of east China's Jiangsu province, is
sponsoring an exhibition on Hong Kong with over 300 pictures and
100 other objects.
</P>
<P>
Some of the historical objects are shown in public for the
first time. The include "boundary stones of British concessions",
and a portrait of General Guan Tianpei who died a heroic death in
the First Opium War launched by British aggressors from 1840 to
1842.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also shows cooperation between Jiangsu and Hong
Kong in the fields of economy, culture, medical care, and
education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0192 </DOCNO>
