<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of China Supports Foreign Trade Enterprises in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The local branch of Bank of
China in the central Henan Province raised massive funds to
bolster money-losing foreign trade enterprises, with results.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, the province's foreign
trade enterprises earned a total of 640 million US dollars in
foreign exchange, backed by 1.76 billion yuan (220 million
dollars) in bank loans.
</P>
<P>
Bank experts say that many local foreign trade enterprises in
Henan have been trapped in loss-making in recent years, and most
of their loans remained overdue.
</P>
<P>
So the bank adopted measures to continue making loans to both
the profit-making enterprises, and the poor, according to bank
officials.
</P>
<P>
Most of the bank's newly-added loans this year have been used
to support the export of industrial and agricultural products with
low cost and high added-value, according to the officials.
</P>
<P>
The bank issued a total of 90 million yuan in loans to aid
export of textiles, silk, grain, and oil in the first four months
of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
