<HEADLINE> Hebei Uses More Overseas Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has signed direct investment contracts involving 2.65 billion US
dollars at a recent trade fair.
</P>
<P>
About 526 companies from 48 countries and regions attended the
97' Hebei Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Fair.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong business people are the most active among the
overseas participants in the event," local trade officials said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong business people signed a total of 348 projects with
local Chinese partners at the fair, and the contractual value of
these projects reached 840 million US dollars, accounting for one
third of the total, they said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the overseas investors show keen interest in local
industrial and infrastructure projects, the sources said, adding
that a total of 679 industrial projects have been signed.
</P>
<P>
"Hebei has made great progress in attracting overseas capital,"
Cong Fukui, deputy governor of the province, said.
</P>
<P>
Cong said that investment from Japan, Singapore, the United
States, and Germany has also been increasing in the province.
