<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nomination for Indian Presidential Election Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Indian Vice-President K. R.
Narayanan, former chief election commissioner T. N. Seshan and 60
others have filed their nominations for the 11th presidential
elections as nominations for the race closed on Monday, The
Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
Scrutiny of the nominations will begin today and the last date
for withdrawal is June 26.
</P>
<P>
Sources here said only the nomination papers of Narayanan,
Seshan and three others had the mandatory list of 50 proposers and
50 seconders from among the members of the electoral college.
</P>
<P>
The electoral college comprises 543 members from the Lok Sabha
(the lower house of the parliament), 233 from the Rajya Sabha (the
upper house) and 4,072 members of the legislative assemblies in
states and union territories.
</P>
<P>
All the three major political formations in the country, namely
the ruling United Front, the Congress party and the Bharatiya
Janata Party, have filed nomination papers in support of Narayanan
as the presidential candidate.
</P>
<P>
According to The Hindustan Times, more than 87 percent of the
members of the electoral college have announced their support for
Narayanan's candidature, making his election to the country's
highest office a foregone conclusion.
</P>
<P>
However, the election of the president, by the electoral
college, will proceed as scheduled on July 14 if two or more
candidates remain on the list.  
</P>
</TEXT>
