<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales Up in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The value of total retail sales
in Hong Kong in April 1997, estimated at 18.4 billion HK dollars
(2.37 billion US dollars), increased nine percent from April 1996,
according to the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
After discounting the effect of price changes over the period,
total retail sales increased by five percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with a year ago, sales of motor vehicles continued to
record a significant increase, by 46 percent in both value and
volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales of jewellery, watches and clocks and valuable gifts also
surged, by 15 percent in value and 16 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with March 1997, total retail sales in April 1997
decreased by two percent in value and three percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing with the period from January to April 1997 with the
same period in 1996, total retail sales rose by seven percent in
value and three percent in volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
