<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Strengthens Economic Cooperation with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi, an energy base in northern
China, has listed coking, metallurgy, tourism and automobile
industries as fields for cooperation with Hong Kong and other
overseas regions and countries.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between Shanxi and Hong Kong reached 210
million US dollars last year, which made Hong Kong the second
biggest trade partner of the province.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Shanxi registered 920 Hong Kong funded
projects, 54 percent of Shanxi's overseas funded projects. The
province used 749 million dollars from Hong Kong, one third of its
total introduced from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen have extended their investment from raw
materials to infrastructure like energy and communications. The
province launched last year two Hong Kong funded highway projects
which will absorb a total of 60 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, large state-owned enterprises in Shanxi began to
issue H-shares on the Hong Kong stock exchange.
</P>
<P>
The province has been exporting to Hong Kong quality coal,
coking products, iron and steel products, building materials and
textile products for years. In the past two years, Shanxi's
machinery, electronic, and telecommunications equipment were
welcomed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi has been importing equipment and raw materials from Hong
Kong in the past few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
