<HEADLINE> 233 Vietnamese Sent Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Two groups totaling 233
Vietnamese returned by air to Hanoi, Vietnam, today on the 107th
and 108th flights under the Orderly Repatriation Program (ORP).
The returnees include 217 illegal immigrants and 16 migrants and
comprise 220 men, 11 women, one boy and one girl.
</P>
<P>
Most of them arrived in Hong Kong this year. Some came last
year and in 1991, 1990, 1989 and 1988.
</P>
<P>
The two groups brought to 10,843 the total number repatriated
on ORP flights since November 1991.
</P>
<P>
According to Hong Kong Government Information Services, there
are now 3,462 Vietnamese migrants and illegal immigrants in Hong
Kong.  
