<HEADLINE> Ethnic Literature Flourishes in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- More writers from ethnic groups in
southwest China's Yunnan Province have appeared in recent years.
</P>
<P>
There are 224 ethnic writers in the Provincial Writers'
Association, nearly a quarter of the membership.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has 25 ethnic groups with a population of 13.3 million,
one third of the province's total. The ethnic groups only had oral
literary traditions until 1970s. To date, the ethnic writers have
published seven novels and 15 book collections.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 120 such writers have attended training
programs at colleges and universities. 
</P>
