<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebel Hit Squad Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have arrested
six members of a Tamil rebel hit squad in Colombo and will mount
operations to round up rebel suspects who have slipped into the
capital, police sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The six hit men, who were arrested at two lodging houses in the
business center of Pettah yesterday, took part in several attacks
in Jaffna and arrived for "disruptive activities" in Colombo in
the wake of the military's new round of Operation Jaya Sikuru in
Northern Province.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain of Victory)
was launched by government troops on May 13 to open a key supply
line along a highway linking Vavuniya to the Jaffna Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Police are now interrogating the six rebels suspects.
Meanwhile, police will conduct operations in Colombo and suburbs
to round up rebel elements who have infiltrated into the capital
city, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a 14-year war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country.  
</P>
