The talks, said the Ecuadoran Defense Ministry in a communique,
would last through Saturday behind closed doors at a military base
in Sangolqui, the southeastern section of Quito.
</P>
<P>
Heading the delegates were the chiefs of the joint command of
armed forces from both countries, General Paco Moncayo of Ecuador
and General Jorge Nadal Palva of Peru.
</P>
<P>
The same groups of high-ranking officers were at the first
round of talks between the two militaries in Lima, capital of
Peru, on September 22-28, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing second round was expected to develop a concept of
integral South American security for closer military cooperation
between the two countries, the defense ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
