<DOCNO> XIE19970624.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Briefs From Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The following are news briefs
from the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) in the past few days:
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Starting June 20, Uruguay will become the pro
tempore president of Mercosur for the next six months.
</P>
<P>
For Uruguay, the priority of its term will be to facilitate the
Chilean and Bolivian participation in negotiations with other
blocs, though the two are not full members of this free trade
group.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Mercosur countries will take joint action to
confront the emerging diseases, such as dengue fever, and
coordinate epidemiological control on their common borders.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the Public Health Ministers from Argentina,
Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay held on June 18 in Asuncion, capital
of Paraguay, the ministers agreed to form a technical working
group in charge of establishing joint actions and an agreement on
medicine with extra-regional countries.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The governments of Brazil and Bolivia signed a
memorandum on environmental cooperation here on June 18.
</P>
<P>
Under the document, the two countries decided to create
a sub-program of technical cooperation on sustainable development
and to foster the increase of information on the environment, and
improve the potential utilization of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- On June 18 Argentine President Carlos Menem and
his Paraguayan counterpart, Juan Carlos Wasmosy, signed agreements
on defense, job creation on common borders and international
security to intensify their bilateral relations and regional
integration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
