<HEADLINE> DDC Elections in Nepal Postponed Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Election Commission of Nepal
has postponed once again the district development committees (DDC)
elections from July 11 until July 19, local press reports said
today.
</P>
<P>
As the scheduled date coincides with the presentation of the
budget in parliament and the vote on accounts bill, the commission
agreed to a request from the Lower House Business Advisory
Committee to put off the elections after discussing with the
recognized political parties.
</P>
<P>
The DDC elections had been rescheduled from June 20 to July 11.
</P>
<P>
The local elections in Nepal have been divided into three
phases. Elections in 3,192 village development committees (VDC)
and 58 municipalities took place on May 17 and 26 respectively,
while the elections for 75 DDCs in four of the five development
regions have been put off twice.  
</P>
