<HEADLINE> Thai Military Introduces Voluntary Retirement Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Thai military has introduced a
program to allow high-ranking officers in the armed forces to
retire voluntarily.
</P>
<P>
The program, initiated by Prime Minister and Defense Minister
Chavalit Yongchaiyudh, won the approval by the Defense Council on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, those generals deemed suitable for voluntary
retirement will be promoted to higher ranks before they retire to
allow them to receive pensions according to their new ranks.
</P>
<P>
Officers with the rank of major general who retire voluntarily
will be promoted to the rank of general, while those with the rank
of rear-admiral or air vice marshal will be promoted to admiral or
air chief marshal.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said the move is part of Chavalit's plan to
reduce the armed forces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
