<HEADLINE> Singaporean Housewife Jailed For Sex With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 24 (Xinhua) -- In the first case of its kind in
Singapore, a woman was sentenced to a six-month jail term on
Monday for committing an obscene act of having sex with a
13-year-old boy, the Straits Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that housewife Yu Chiew Tuan, 33, pleaded
guilty tearfully to what is believed to be the first case of its
kind under the Children and Young Persons Act. She had sex with
the boy brought home by her husband "to please her" in July last
year.
</P>
<P>
Yu Chiew Tuan's lawyer reportedly said that she had never
thought it was an offense to have sex with a boy. To her, she was
merely having sex with a consenting party.
</P>
<P>
However, District Judge S. Thyagarajan said sexual exploitation
of children must be punished severely.
</P>
<P>
The Straits Times report said that police discovered the
offense on January 7, this year.
</P>
<P>
Chua Peng Huey, Yu's 43-year-old husband, was then a night
guard in a children's home and he had molested four boys aged
between 12 and 14, for which he is serving a sentence of 42 months
and eight strokes of the cane. He had taken one of the boys home
for his wife.
</P>
<P>
At Chua's hearing in March, counsel had told the court in
mitigation that he took the victim home to "please his wife" as he
could not satisfy her sex demands. Their sex problem had created
tension in the marriage and he was worried she would leave him for
another man.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
