<HEADLINE> BA Opens Branch in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of America (BA) opened a
branch office in Beijing Monday, its third in China, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The move is intended to capture a larger market share of the
country's growing investment banking business, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Coming from a traditional commercial banking business, the
US-based bank has joined a trend in the world's banking circle to
expand its investment banking services, which is more lucrative
than commercial banking.
</P>
<P>
In China, local firms' increasing fund-raising activities in
the capital markets have also encouraged BA operation officials
in China to expand their investment banking services here, said
bank chairman David Coulter.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing branch, which covers northern and northeastern
China, will seek clients interested in using capital markets as a
funding source.
</P>
<P>
Beijing branch officials said they are already discussing
fund-raising programs with some enterprises in northeast China,
one of the country's largest industrial hubs.
</P>
<P>
The bank's first and second branches in China are located in
Shanghai and Guangzhou. It also has a representative office in
Dalian, a coastal city in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
