<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Strengthening Land Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province has created additional 68,000 hectares of farmland in the
last seven years thanks to its stronger land management measures.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government said that the
province has demarcated farmland protection zones in 78 cities and
counties, covering 100 million hectares or accounting for 86
percent of the province's total farmland.
</P>
<P>
The province has issued two local laws and quite a number of
local regulations and local government decrees concerning the
management and protection of farmland. The provincial government
has dealt with 12,000 cases involving illegal use of land and
pulled down 610,000 bootleg structures, recovering 1,500 hectares
of land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
