<HEADLINE> Steels Wins Swiss Cycling Seventh Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Belgium's Tom Steels took the
seventh stage of the Tour of Switzerland cycling race on Monday
while France's Christophe Agnolutto kept his overall lead.
</P>
<P>
Steels completed the 194-km stage from Locarno to Zug in five
hours 25 minutes and 13 seconds, beating second-placed German Erik
Zabel by a bike-length.
</P>
<P>
Agnolutto moved closer to his first major Tour victory when he
finished 21st, in the same time as the winner. He led by five
minutes 14 seconds over Switzerland's Oskar Camenzind in the
overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Jan Ullrich stayed third, six minutes 15 seconds
behind the leader. 
</P>
