<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tri-National Commission Meets on River Basin Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Experts from Argentina,
Paraguay and Bolivia today gathered in the province of Tucuman,
Argentina, and began discussion of the development of the upper
basin of the Pilcomayo River.
</P>
<P>
It is the fourth meeting of experts from a tri-national
committee set up to promote sustainable development of the
Pilcomayo basin and to explore natural resources there.
</P>
<P>
The meeting focused on the implementation of the three
countries' joint projects that deal with flooding, retention of
sediments and the regulation of water flows.
</P>
<P>
Also taking part in the meeting were representatives of
international financial organizations and natural resource
projects of public institutions and universities.
</P>
<P>
The Pilcomayo River, a major South American river system, flows
2,500 kilometers through agricultural zones in the three
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
