<HEADLINE> Petrol Prices in Italy Highest Among Nine European Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Italy returned to the top of the
European petrol price league in May, with super grade costing
1,908 lire (1.13 U.S. dollars) a liter and unleaded 1,818 lire
(1.07 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the nine countries in the league, Spain was the least
expensive with 1,401 lire in the same grade.
</P>
<P>
However, Italian drivers with diesel engined vehicles were
better off, with a liter costing 1,430 lire, the same with the
European Union average, less than Switzerland's 1,473, Britain's
1,645 and Ireland's 1,452.  
</P>
</TEXT>
