<HEADLINE> British Organization Aids Medicare in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Health Unlimited, a British
non-governmental organization, will donate seven million yuan
(about 843,000 US dollars) to help improve medicare in remote
areas of southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The organization signed an agreement with Yunnan's health
department to kick off the health-promotion project. The money
will be spent on training local hospital personnel and students at
vocational medical schools in Baoshan and Dehong prefectures over
the next four years.
</P>
<P>
They will study simple child-delivery skills and treatment of
common diseases.
</P>
<P>
The two areas have a population of 3.5 million and have had
fairly high mortality rates among infants, pregnant women, and
women in labor because of poor medical services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
