<HEADLINE> Calender of Men's Volleyball World League Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- As three pool preliminaries
concluded over the weekend, six teams have qualified for the men's
volleyball World League Finals slated from June 30 to July 5 in
Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Pool winners of Brazil, Cuba and Italy book their respective
berths, and Russia enters as the host, replacing Yugoslavia, the
lowest-scoring second-placers.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria and Netherlands, both on 21 points, secured their
outing as Yugoslavia was eliminated on 20 points from the pool
preliminaries.
</P>
<P>
The six-team finals will be played in round robin, with each
playing four matches against teams from other preliminary groups.
</P>
<P>
Top two teams after the round-robin tournament, will vie for
the 1997 World League Champion title and a bonus of 1,000,000 US
dollars on July 5, with teams ranked third and fourth to vie for
the bronze medal and a prize money of 200,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Following are the calender of 1997 World League finals:
</P>
<P>
