<HEADLINE> Hainan Accelerates Pace of Meilan Airport Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Meilan
international airport in Haikou, capital of the southernmost
China's Hainan Province, is proceeding well and at a rapid rate as
an investment of 546 million or 23 percent of the total investment
has been made.
</P>
<P>
Estimated to cost 2.3 billion yuan, the first phase project
began early this year and is scheduled for completion toward the
end of next year.
</P>
<P>
The airport is designed to cover 560 ha. of land, with a runway
measuring 3,600 meters long and 45 meters wide, and a terminal building
with a floor space of 60,000 square meters. It will be able to
accommodate Boeing 747-400.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to become one of the trunk line airport in China
and a large international airport in the Asian-Pacific Region.
</P>
</TEXT>
