<HEADLINE> South China Region Increasing Machinery and Electronics Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region exported 251 million US dollar worth of
machinery and electronics products last year, a significant
increase from 8.27 million US dollar worth in 1985.
</P>
<P>
During recent years, the province has issued a series of
policies to encourage the export of local machinery and
electronics products and the use of overseas investment, advanced
technology and large-scaled technological improvements in
producing export products.
</P>
<P>
The region invested more than 81 million yuan in 12
technology-upgrading projects in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Of the 41 major export-oriented enterprises in the sector, 39
have been empowered to handle their own exports.
</P>
<P>
More than three-fourths of the exports are products with high
added value, including ships, completed sets of equipment,
household electrical appliances, TVs, and audio equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
