<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hi-tech Industry New Economic Center in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- China's pioneer special economic
zone next-door to Hong Kong has seen many changes in its
industries in past years, and its hi-tech industries are expected
to help sustain economic growth in future, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
The city's hi-tech industrial turnover was 34.8 billion yuan in
1996, up 54 percent from the previous year, and output value of
hi-tech products accounted for 28.7 percent of the total
industrial output value, a rise of 8.2 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The information industry is now a major part of the hi-tech
sector, where industrial turnover last year was 26.4 billion yuan,
a year-on-year rise of 52 percent. Other fast-growing sectors
include bio-engineering and new materials.
</P>
<P>
To maintain the steady growth, the city developed a series of
policies and increased the amount of land. In addition to a
hi-tech industrial village, the city set up a new
11.5-sq.km. hi-tech development district to the west of the city,
while local government and enterprises spent 9.2 billion yuan on
research and development.
</P>
<P>
The city has 259 enterprises producing and developing hi-tech
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
