<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Have English Newspaper on July 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital city of
south China's Guangdong Province, will have its own English
newspaper beginning July 1.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Morning Post, to be published every Friday, will
report on the latest economic, social and political developments
in Guangzhou, the Pearl River Delta, and South China.
</P>
<P>
In March 1996, Guangzhou Daily began to print its English
version. The paper decided to upgrade its English version to a
newspaper after finding growing enthusiasm for local English media
as the local foreign expatriate community demands more knowledge
about Guangzhou and nearby regions.  
