<HEADLINE> Foreign Capital Investment Up In Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Foreign capital investment in
Argentina hit 21.5 billion U.S. dollars in May, up 74.7 percent
from the same period last year, said the National Securities
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Belgium was the biggest source of foreign capital investment
with 7.65 billion dollars or 32.86 percent of the total, said the
commission in a report published today.
</P>
<P>
The United States was second with 7.16 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Investments made by residents in Argentina increased at a lower
pace, with 6 percent in stocks and 10.7 in public securities,
according to the commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
