<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meteorological Service for Airports Increased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- After July 1, meteorological
stations at ten major Chinese airports will report local climate
conditions every half an hour from 8:00 to 24:00, instead of every
one hour previously, according to the Civil Aviation
Administration of China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
The cities are Guangzhou, Beijing, Taiyuan, Shanghai, Tianjin,
Hangzhou, Shenzhen, Shenyang, Dalian, and Urumqi.
</P>
<P>
The more detailed weather forecast will provide pilots and air
traffic controllers the latest climate information that will
ensure safety of flights, said a meteorological engineer with CAAC.
</P>
<P>
CAAC made such a decision in response to the sharp increase in
the volume of traffic at Chinese airports in recent years, as well
as requirements of the International Civil Aviation Organization.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
