<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Shakes US Seattle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring
4.8 on the Richter scale shook Seattle area today, with no
immediate reports of injuries or damage.
</P>
<P>
The tremor occurred at 12:13 p.m. PDT (1913 GMT) and was
centered at the Puget Sound area, 24 kilometers west of Seattle,
according to the U.S. Geological Survey.
</P>
<P>
It was the most serious earthquake in the region since May 2,
1996, when a 5.5 quake shook the northeast of Seattle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
