<HEADLINE> US Urges Iraq to Heed UN Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The United States today called
on Iraq to heed the warning issued by the U.N. Security Council
this weekend and cooperate with U.N. inspectors, or it will face
penalties.
</P>
<P>
"The Security Council has sent a clear message to Iraq: when
the authority of the Security Council is challenged, it will react
in a decisive manner," State Department spokesman John Dinger told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council passed a resolution Saturday condemning
Iraq's refusal to grant members of the U.N. Special Commission
(UNSCOM) access to certain sites for their inspection, and
threatened to impose further sanctions on Iraq next October if
Baghdad continued obstructing the inspectors' activities in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"We want Iraq to recognize the seriousness of this message and
to cooperate fully with the UNSCOM," Dinger said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement carried by local media today, Iraq's
Revolutionary Command Council, which met Sunday night, rejected
the U.N. Security Council resolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
