<HEADLINE> Former US Senate Leader Visits Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Former U.S. senate majority
leader Bob Dole visited Sarajevo today for discussions with
Bosnian officials on the implementation of the Dayton peace
agreement.
</P>
<P>
Dole, who was also the Republican presidential candidate in
1996, met with Chairman of the Bosnian Presidency Alija
Izetbegovic, Co-chairman of the Council of Ministers Haris
Silajdzic and other Bosnian officials.
</P>
<P>
According to local press reports, Dole told his hosts that he
backs the Clinton administration's policy of conditioning
assistance on the openness of cities to all people, regardless of
religious or national backgrounds.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the United States would not like to see the
politization of army, Islamic exclusivity within the governmental
structures or a decrease in the number of Croat and Serb employees
in government institutions, the reports said. 
</P>
